</span></div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here, **Then** indicates that the sentence it introduces explains the results of what the previous sentences described. Alternate translation: [As a result]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The implication is that King Darius ordered his officials to search in the royal archives to investigate the claims that the Jewish elders had made in response to the questions that Tattenai and his associates asked them. If it would be helpful to your readers, you could say this explicitly. Alternate translation: [King Darius commanded his officials to investigate whether King Cyrus had issued a 
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> **Darius** is the name of a man. See how you translated it in 4:5.
