    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> It is no longer clear exactly what these building instructions mean. They could mean that the walls of the temple should be three layers of stone thick, with a facing of wood on the inside. They could also mean that the walls should be built with one layer of wood on top of every three layers of stone, or that the temple was to have four stories, the lower three of stone and the top one of wood. W
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here, **house** is a metaphor for property, meaning everything that a person keeps in his house, and by extension, everything that he owns. So **house** in this context represents the wealth and income of the king. Alternate translation: [I will pay the expenses from the royal revenue]
    </div>
