      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here the word **And** indicates that the event the story will now relate came after the event it has just described. If it would be helpful in your language, you could show this relationship by using a word such as “Then.”
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here, **stand** is a figurative way of saying that a person has assumed the duties of their office. So to cause someone to stand is to appoint them to those duties and install them in that office. Alternate translation: [And they appointed the priests … and the Levites]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here, **they** refers to the leaders of the Jews. Alternate translation: [And the leaders of the Jews appointed the priests] or [Then the Jewish elders established the priests]
